omic Freedom).<ref name=\"2014 Index of Economic Freedom\" />]]\nPublic social spending comprises cash benefits, direct in-kind provision of goods and services, and tax breaks with social purposes provided by general government (that is central, state, and local governments, including social security funds).<ref name=SSP2015>{{cite web |title=Social spending Public, % of GDP, 2015 |publisher=OECD |url=https://data.oecd.org/chart/4Tcd }} [https://data.oecd.org/socialexp/social-spending.htm OECD data]</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-right:auto;text-align: right\"\n|+ 2015 Public social spending, OECD<ref name=SSP2015/>\n!Country !! Public social spending<br />% of GDP\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| FRA}} || 31.7\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| FIN}} || 30.6\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| BEL}} || 29.2\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| ITA}} || 28.9\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| DNK}} || 28.8\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| AUT}} || 28.0\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| SWE}} || 26.7\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| GRC}} || 26.4\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| ESP}} || 25.4\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| DEU}} || 25.0\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| PRT}} || 24.1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| NOR}} || 23.9\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| SVN}} || 22.4\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| NLD}} || 22.3\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| LUX}} || 22.2\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| GBR}} || 21.5\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|OECD || 21.0\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| HUN}} || 20.7\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| NZL}} || 19.7\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| CHE}} || 19.6\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| CZE}} || 19.5\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| POL}} || 19.4\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| SVK}} || 19.4\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| USA}} || 19.0\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| AUS}} || 18.8\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry| CAN}} || 17.2