hose affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"Metro-12521241\">{{cite web |title=Children In Need and Comic Relief join forces for first time for coronavirus |url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/04/07/children-need-comic-relief-join-forces-first-time-coronavirus-relief-12521241/ |website=Metro |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Independent-a9474766\">{{cite news |title=BBC Big Night In: Peter Kay, Little Britain and Vicar of Dibley to return for special charity event - follow live |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/bbc-big-night-in-live-stream-channel-best-bits-peter-kay-little-britain-catch-up-watch-a9474766.html |accessdate=23 April 2020 |work=The Independent |date=23 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> The British government will match all public donations, with a minimum of \u00a320 million.<ref name=\"BBC-52379802\">{{cite web |title=Doctor Who stars unite for BBC's Big Night In |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-52379802 |website=BBC News |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt is the first joint initiative between two BBC telethon charities, [[Children in Need]] and [[Comic Relief]].<ref name=\"Metro-12521241\" /> The [[showrunner]] and [[executive producer]] for the BBC is Peter Davey.<ref name=\"YLG2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/leisure/showbiz/18400491.foo-fighters-praise-live-lounge-charity-cover-ahead-bbcs-big-night/|title=Foo Fighters praise Live Lounge charity cover ahead of BBC\u2019s Big Night In|work=Your Local Guardian|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Presenters and performers ==\nThe scheduled presenters include [[Lenny Henry]], [[Matt Baker]], [[Zoe Ball]], [[Davina McCall]] and [[Paddy McGuinness]].<ref name=\"Metro-12558735\" /> Most of those appearing will take part remotely, via [[Videotelephony|video links]], while the studio presenters will maintain [[social distancing]].<ref name=\"Independent-a9474766\" /> There will be comedy appearances by [[Steve Coogan]], [[Rob Brydon]], [[Jack Whitehall]], [[Romesh Ranganathan]], and [[Miranda Hart]],<ref name=\"BBC-52379802\" /> as well as music performances from [[Sam Smith]] and [[Celeste (singer)|Celeste]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/bignightin/theshow|title=Big Night In: The Show|website=BBC|url-status=live|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Line-up ==\nExcluding \"surprise\" appearances from guests like [[Mary Berry]] and [[Little Mix]], [[BBC]]'s advertised line-up is as follows:<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\"Metro-12558735\" /><ref name=\"ES-LB\">{{cite web |title=Little Britain to return to TV for Big Night In charity telethon |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/stayingin/tvfilm/little-britain-comeback-big-night-in-bbc-a4416191.html |website=Evening Standard |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC-52379802\" /><ref name=\"Beaumont-Thomas\">{{cite news |last1=Beaumont-Thomas |first1=Ben |title=BBC Radio 1 launches coronavirus charity song with Dua Lipa, Chris Martin and more |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/apr/20/bbc-radio-1-launches-coronavirus-charity-song-with-dua-lipa-chris-martin-and-more |accessdate=23 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[Miranda Hart]] and the cast of ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]].''\n* A lockdown sermon by ''[[The Vicar of Dibley]]'' featuring [[Dawn French]].\n* Premiere of the video for [[Live Lounge Allstars]]' [[Times Like These (Live Lounge Allstars charity single)|cover version]] of Foo Fighter's \"Times Like These\"\n* [[Steve Coogan]] and [[Rob Brydon]] in ''[[The Trip (2010 TV series)|The Trip]]''.\n* [[Catherine Tate]] and [[David Tennant]] perform: \"[[Lauren Cooper|Lauren]] the \u2018[[Am I bovvered|Am I Bovvered]]\u2019 teenager gets home-schooled\"\n* [[Matt Lucas]] and the [[BBC Orchestras and Singers|BBC Orchestra]] perform \"Baked Potato Song\"\n*[[Sam Smith]] performs \"[[Lay Me Down (Sam Smith song)|Lay Me Down]]\"\n*Celeste performs a cover of Bill Withers' \"[[Lean on Me (song)|Lean On Me]]\"\n*[[Jack Whitehall]] in [[Bad Education (TV series)|''Bad Education'']] with [[Mathew Horne|Matthew Horne]] and [[Anthony Joshua]]\n*''[[People Just Do Nothing]]''\n*[[EastEnders]] pub quiz in the [[Queen Vic Fire Week|Queen Vic]] hosted by [[Ian Beale]]\n*[[Peter Kay]] and the British public remake the \"[[(Is This the Way to) Amarillo|Is This the Way to Amarillo]]\" video\n*The first televisual ''[[Little Britain]]'' sketch for over a decade\n*[[Tess Daly]] and [[Claudia Winkleman]] do host a ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'' choreography challenge\n*[[Romesh Ranganathan]]'s Isolation Diary\n*[[Joe Wicks (coach)|Joe Wicks]]' exercise secrets\n*a reunion of actors who have played the title role in [[Doctor Who]] salute [[National Health Service|NHS]] health workers.\n*Stand-up at home from [[Jason Manford]], [[Rosie Jones (comedian)|Rosie Jones]], [[Tez Ilyas]], [[Dane Baptiste]], [[Russell Kane]], The Lost Voice Guy, [[Nish Kumar]] and more\n*[[Liam Payne]], [[Olly Murs]], [[Leona Lewis]], [[Nicole Scherzinger]], [[Freya Ridings]], [[Katherine Jenkins]], [[Alfie Boe]], [[Gregory Porter]] and more join [[Gary Barlow]] to perform \"[[Sing (Gary Barlow song)|Sing]]\"\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n*{{Official website}}\n*{{BBC programme}}\n*{{IMDb title|tt12183158}}\n<!--\n{{Children in Need}}\n{{Comic Relief}} please wait until after broadcast, so we can make best use of 'what links here' -->\n\n[[Category:Telethons]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Children in Need]]\n[[Category:Comic Relief]]\n[[Category:BBC Television programmes]]\n[[Category:British telethons]]\n[[Category:2020 in British television]]\n[[Category:2020 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2020 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Charity e